Get All Translations for a Locale

Source: R/localization.R
get_translations.Rd

Returns all available translations for the specified or current locale. Useful for reviewing available translation keys and their values.

Usage

get_translations(locale = NULL, include_custom = TRUE)

Arguments

locale

Character or NULL. Locale to retrieve translations for. If NULL (default), uses the current locale.

include_custom

Logical. Whether to include custom translations added via add_translation() (default: TRUE).

Value

A named list of all translations where names are keys and values are translated strings.

See also

tr(), add_translation(), set_locale()

Examples

# Get all English translations
translations <- get_translations("en")
names(translations)[1:10]
#>  [1] "study_drug" "treatment"  "statistic"  "parameter"  "category"  
#>  [6] "placebo"    "total"      "value"      "variable"   "subgroup"  

# Get current locale translations
get_translations()
